    "body": "I would like to propose [these contracts](https://github.com/RubiconDeFi/rubicon_protocol/tree/master/contracts/proxy) as OVM-safe, transparent, and upgradeable proxies for use on Optimism.\r\n\r\nThe only changes I made to the OZ stack were to the core \"Proxy\" contract, hence my changing the contract name to OVMProxy. I took the `delegate` functionality from [this OP contract](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/8d67991aba584c1703692ea46273ea8a1ef45f56/packages/contracts/contracts/optimistic-ethereum/OVM/accounts/OVM_ProxyEOA.sol#L57) and applied it to the OZ stack in [`_delegate`](https://github.com/RubiconDeFi/rubicon_protocol/blob/32388b4231ac8da6d64aeff3cf78b901f4dedf68/contracts/proxy/OVMProxy.sol#L21). These contracts compile correctly in the OVM and have worked while implemented in my test network project on Optimism Kovan.\r\n\r\nPlease let me know what the correct procedure here is to make a PR or share this in the repo if interested.",
